The paper deals with wireless access points on unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) for mobile service provisioning in commercial networks. It involves modeling a network of UAVs operating at a certain height above ground to provide wireless service within coverage areas shaped by their directional antennas, with the UAVs using the existing terrestrial base station network for wireless backhaul. This involves concepts related to network infrastructure (NI), information theory (IT), mathematical analysis (MA), systems and control (SY), and multimedia (MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI, followed by cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
